Dorsum (
Fig. 71
). Both prodorsum and opisthosoma with dorsocentral and lateral rugose ridges, separated by reticulations. Dorsal body setae broadly lanceolate and strongly serrate. Prodorsal projection deeply notched (notch not reaching setae
v 2
), forming two broad triangular lobes, with small lateral lobes.

Gnathosoma (
Fig. 74
). Infracapitulum reaching middle to anterior margin of genu I. Palp four-segmented; palp tarsus with two eupathidia and a seta, tibia with two setae, femorogenu with one seta and trochanter without setae.

