Figs 75–77
). Counts of setae and solenidia (included in counts) on podomeres of legs I–IV: coxae 2 - 2 - 1 - 1 , trochanters 1 - 1-2 - 1 , femora 4 - 4 - 2 - 1 , genua 3 - 3 - 1 -0, tibiae 5 - 5 - 3 - 3 , tarsi 9 (ω)- 9 (ω)- 5 - 5 . Leg chaetotaxy as follows: trochanters I, II, IV v’ ; tr III v’, l’ ; femora I–II d, v’, bv” , l’ ; fe III d, ev ’; fe IV ev ’; genua I–II l’, d, l” ; ge III l’ ; ge IV nude; tibiae I–II d, l’, l” v’, v”; ti III–IV d, v’, v”; tarsus I–II u’, u”, p’, p” tc’, tc”, ft’ , ft”, ω ; ta III–IV u’, u”, tc’, tc”, ft’ . Dorsal setae on femora I–II broadly lanceolate and strongly serrate, and on genua I–II narrowly lanceolate and serrate.

